        <div class="space-y-3">
          <h3 class="text-xs font-semibold text-ink uppercase tracking-wider font-mono">What is a Good Typing Speed? Understanding the Metrics</h3>
          <p class="text-justify">
            If you have ever wondered, "<strong>whats a good typing speed</strong>?", the answer depends on your professional role and daily computer usage. The global average typing speed sits at approximately 40 words per minute (WPM). For casual computer users, this is sufficient. However, for professionals, developers, and data specialists, a competitive benchmark starts at 60 to 80 WPM. Elite typists and transcriptionists often exceed 100 WPM, with some of the world's competitive champions reaching a <strong>fastest typing speed</strong> of over 200 WPM. By using our tool to measure your <strong>average wpm typing speed</strong>, you can set realistic training benchmarks. Progressing from an <strong>average typing speed</strong> to an advanced speed of 80+ WPM can save you hours of writing time every single week, helping you complete tasks with greater ease.
