          <p class="text-justify">
            To ensure objective results across different languages and text selections, we calculate your speed based on the official global standard. Under this standard, one word is defined as exactly 5 keystrokes, which includes spaces, punctuation, and return keys. This standardizes testing variations regardless of word complexity. If you type 250 characters in one minute, your raw speed is calculated as 50 WPM. Accuracy is equally crucial; our strict error-handling mode blocks cursor movement on typos, training your fingers to self-correct immediately. This stops the reinforcement of bad habits and ensures your net words per minute calculations are built on solid accuracy.
          </p>
